Adds a 'What's NOT licensed in this fork' section to LICENSE.md making
the fork's posture explicit for future readers. Five sub-sections:

1. License is, and stays, AGPL-3.0-or-later — no dual-licensing.
2. No Contributor License Agreement — divergence from the upstream
   pattern (Astrolabe Cloud's CLA enabling future commercial dual-
   licensing). Contributors retain copyright to their own changes; no
   relicensing power transferred. Functional guarantee of permanent
   AGPL status as contributors accumulate.
3. No paid-tier features — no license check, no trial mode, no feature-
   flag service.
4. No telemetry, no beacon, no Enterprise Edition branch.
5. What this means for upstream contributions — fork-only changes need
   no CLA; upstream PRs would individually require Astrolabe CLA sign.

Schema-versioned 'fork-license-posture-v1'; material changes (e.g. adding
a CLA, switching license) require a major-version bump in the AI-NOTICE
Schema-Version field across all source files.

Authored after the v0.2 plan audit (2026-04-27) revealed that the
upstream's CLA at CLA.md is the most ethically-relevant 'gate' on the
project — runtime code is fully AGPL, but the CLA collects copyrights
broad enough to enable Astrolabe Cloud's dual-licensing future. This
fork opts out of that posture.

Refs:
- Audit details: Documents/Projects/NC/v0.2-plan.md § Gate 4
- Upstream CLA: cbcoutinho/nextcloud-mcp-server/CLA.md
- Triggering question (Gary, 2026-04-27): 'What functionality is
  license-gated... what are the ethical considerations with AGPL 3.0?'
